我们没必要进行这段对话 对吧？
supposed to be having this conversation, right?

1647
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:16,610
俄勒冈州一半的土地 都是受联邦政府保护的
Half of Oregon is protected Federal parkland.

1648
01:10:16,620 --> 01:10:18,030
他们没办法拉拢
They can't develop it.

1649
01:10:18,120 --> 01:10:19,830
那边的州预算都是来自于伐木税收
So, state budgets come from logging revenues.

1650
01:10:19,870 --> 01:10:20,910
- 这我知道…  - 莉斯？
- got it...  - Liz?

1651
01:10:20,960 --> 01:10:23,070
你现在先不要想这些 这次辩论与此无关
Whatever clearing your head looks like, this isn't it.

1652
01:10:23,460 --> 01:10:25,250
所以说伐木工是非常重要的人群
So, loggers are a very influential group.

1653
01:10:25,500 --> 01:10:26,620
打扰一下！
Excuse me!

1654
01:10:26,710 --> 01:10:28,500
能来个人帮她化下妆吗？
Can someone have her makeup done, too, please?

1655
01:10:28,550 --> 01:10:29,630
我又不上电视！
I'm not a part of this!

1656
01:10:29,720 --> 01:10:31,250
摄影棚到处都是摄像机 你也要注意形象
You're a public figure in a room full of cameras.

1657
01:10:31,260 --> 01:10:32,370
是她吗？
IS that her?

1658
01:10:34,260 --> 01:10:35,250
莉斯？
Liz?

1659
01:10:35,810 --> 01:10:37,920
快叫布莱恩去联系那些伐木工
Hey, we have to get Bryan on these loggers.

1660
01:10:38,020 --> 01:10:39,270
我们马上去处理那些伐木工！
We're on top of the goddamn loggers!

1661
01:10:39,270 --> 01:10:40,260
你先给我集中注意！
Just clear your head!

1662
01:10:40,310 --> 01:10:41,300
稍等一下
One moment.

1663
01:10:41,480 --> 01:10:42,980
别胡思乱想 照我说的做
Clear your head, like I told you.

1664
01:10:43,310 --> 01:10:44,350
喂？
Hello?

1665
01:10:47,070 --> 01:10:49,350
- 好了  - 欢迎你 斯隆女士
- Fine.  - Ms. Sloane, welcome.

1666
01:10:49,990 --> 01:10:52,230
帕特 请坐
Pat. Please, take a seat.

1667
01:10:52,820 --> 01:10:54,110
我知道星期五就是提交日期了
I know Friday's Filing Day

1668
01:10:54,200 --> 01:10:55,310
你们组织的运动马上就要结束了
and your campaign will be over,

1669
01:10:55,370 --> 01:10:56,480
但如果你认为我会就此放水的话
but if you're thinking I'm gonna go easy,

1670
01:10:56,530 --> 01:10:57,520
那你就想多了
I can't do that.

1671
01:10:57,910 --> 01:11:00,570
这是现场直播 注意你们的用词
This is live TV, so no colorful language.

1672
01:11:00,660 --> 01:11:02,490
居然拉我的下属下水
Bullshit job offers to my staff,

1673
01:11:02,580 --> 01:11:04,070
你可真是无耻到新下限了
you've plumbed new depths.

1674
01:11:04,170 --> 01:11:05,780
那个自以为是的小姑娘？得了吧
A giant inflatable rodent? Please.

1675
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:07,080
你毁了那个女孩的前程
You ruined that girl's career.

1676
01:11:07,210 --> 01:11:10,500
好了 都给我闭嘴 开始吧！
All right, shut up, the both of you. Let's go!

1677
01:11:15,720 --> 01:11:17,800
大家好 我是乔恩·欧尼尔
Hello, America, I'm Jon O'Neill,

1678
01:11:17,970 --> 01:11:20,840
欢迎收看《华盛顿周报》特别版节目
welcome to a special edition of This Week In Washington.

1679
01:11:21,350 --> 01:11:23,810
枪支！多点还是少点好？
Guns! More or Less?

1680
01:11:23,940 --> 01:11:26,770
去年一共发生了三百七十二起大型的枪击案
There were 372 mass shootings last year,

1681
01:11:26,860 --> 01:11:28,390
六十五起校园枪击案
64 school shootings,

1682
01:11:28,520 --> 01:11:31,390
在美国一共有超过三亿支枪支…
and there are over 300 million guns in our country...

1683
01:11:31,740 --> 01:11:33,150
你以前跟康纳斯共事过？
You used to work with Connors?

1684
01:11:33,240 --> 01:11:34,400
整整四年
Four years.

1685
01:11:34,570 --> 01:11:39,280
满嘴脏话 出其不意 但非常有效率
Foul-mouthed, unexpected, and very effective.

1686
01:11:40,540 --> 01:11:42,990
如果要想背景调查落到实处
If background checks are to be of any use,

1687
01:11:43,080 --> 01:11:45,740
就应该对所有枪支买卖实行 而不是其中的一些
they should apply to all gun sales, not just some.

1688
01:11:45,880 --> 01:11:48,080
这难道不是希顿·哈里斯所推祟的吗？
Isn't that what Heaton-Harris is proposing?

1689
01:11:48,250 --> 01:11:51,840
没错 这条法案确实扩大了枪支管理的范围
Precisely. The bill expands the scope of gun regulation,

1690
01:11:51,920 --> 01:11:53,210
但它同时也是对美国宪法
and it's yet another affront

1691
01:11:53,300 --> 01:11:55,040
所规定的人民合法权利的公开冒犯
to Americans' Constitutional rights.

1692
01:11:55,180 --> 01:11:57,540
不对 这条法案非常有效地
No, the bill closes an absurd loophole

1693
01:11:57,640 --> 01:12:00,000
阻止了恐怖分子黑名单上的人
which allows people on terrorist watch-lists

1694
01:12:00,100 --> 01:12:02,310
在想买枪的时候 不用接受任何检查的漏洞
to buy guns without any checks whatsoever.

1695
01:12:02,390 --> 01:12:04,350
这是对权利政府所规定的的
It's an incursion into individual liberty

1696
01:12:04,440 --> 01:12:05,970
公民自由的一种亵渎…
by an all-powerful government...

1697
01:12:06,060 --> 01:12:08,520
- 什么 就像驾照一样？ - 驾照？
- What, like drivers' licenses?  - Drivers' licenses?

1698
01:12:08,860 --> 01:12:10,270
只有在经受严格的理论教育
It's illegal to operate a car

1699
01:12:10,400 --> 01:12:11,440
以及通过实践考试的人
without going through rigorous

1700
01:12:11,480 --> 01:12:13,100
才能开车 否则就是违法的
theoretical and practical assessments.

1701
01:12:13,400 --> 01:12:15,440
- 这条规则 很显然…  - “河豚厨师”
- That's a clear constraint...  - Fugu chefs.

1702
01:12:15,610 --> 01:12:17,480
…是对公民自由驱车权利的限制
On the freedom of individuals to drive cars,

1703
01:12:17,620 --> 01:12:20,030
- 或者开飞机也是一个道理  - 快说“河豚厨师”
- or pilots to fly planes.  - Come on. Fugu chefs.

1704
01:12:20,120 --> 01:12:22,910
在日本 一名厨师必须经过七年的训练
You know, in Japan, chefs train for seven years

1705
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:24,250
才能为客人准备一种带毒的鱼
before they're allowed to serve

1706
01:12:24,460 --> 01:12:25,710
其名叫河豚
a poisonous blowfish called fug...

1707
01:12:25,750 --> 01:12:26,780
真棒！
Yes!

1708
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:27,950
这跟做背景调查
What does any of this

1709
01:12:28,000 --> 01:12:29,330
有什么关系？
have to do with background checks?

1710
01:12:29,420 --> 01:12:30,910
这是个好问题
Is a fair question.

1711
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:32,160
在座的各位
Does anyone in this room

1712
01:12:32,300 --> 01:12:34,380
有人觉得政府应该废除驾照吗？
think the government should abolish drivers' licenses?

1713
01:12:34,670 --> 01:12:35,910
- 这太荒唐了  - 为什么？
- That's absurd.  - Why?

1714
01:12:36,130 --> 01:12:38,250
驾照也是一种政府对公民自由权利的限制
They're a government incursion into individual liberty.

1715
01:12:38,760 --> 01:12:40,800
我们接受它 是因为它很有道理
We accept them because they make sense.

1716
01:12:40,970 --> 01:12:42,510
对于越危险的机器
The more dangerous the machinery,

1717
01:12:42,600 --> 01:12:44,300
就应该有更严格的测试
the more rigorous the tests should be.

1718
01:12:44,430 --> 01:12:46,170
我觉得我们可以把 对危险机器的定义
I think we can extend our definition

1719
01:12:46,270 --> 01:12:48,980
扩展到半自动武器上来
of dangerous machinery to semi-automatic firearms.

1720
01:12:49,110 --> 01:12:51,020
但是宪法的第二修正案并没有
Except that the Second Amendment to the Constitution

1721
01:12:51,020 --> 01:12:53,400
保护公众驾车的权利
doesn't guarantee the right to drive cars,

1722
01:12:53,530 --> 01:12:57,110
或者操纵机器 亦或是处理河豚
or operate machinery or serve blowfish for that matter.

1723
01:12:57,200 --> 01:13:00,280
