01:32:20,230 --> 01:32:21,850
“你怎么可能预先想到？”
"How could you possibly have known?"

2086
01:32:23,650 --> 01:32:24,990
我是不会这么说的
You're not gonna get it.

2087
01:32:26,950 --> 01:32:28,280
他想杀了我
He wanted to kill me.

2088
01:32:36,460 --> 01:32:38,830
我不知道界限在哪 埃斯米
I didn't know where the line was, Esme.

2089
01:32:45,180 --> 01:32:47,920
我从来都不知道界限在什么地方
I never, never know where the line is.

2090
01:32:57,310 --> 01:32:58,810
你想休息多久都行
Obviously, take all the time you want.

2091
01:32:59,150 --> 01:33:00,180
等你准备好了
And when you're ready,

2092
01:33:00,320 --> 01:33:01,980
我们很欢迎你 重新加入
we'd love to have you back on the campaign.

2093
01:33:02,860 --> 01:33:04,110
这次由你自己选择
Your own terms.

2094
01:33:04,200 --> 01:33:05,780
不用面对媒体 你做幕后工作也行
No media, you can work behind the scenes.

2095
01:33:08,990 --> 01:33:10,660
如果你不想和我共事
If you don't want to work with me,

2096
01:33:12,660 --> 01:33:14,070
我就辞职
I'll resign from the campaign.

2097
01:33:16,620 --> 01:33:17,990
如果这是你所希望的
If that's what you want.

2098
01:33:18,710 --> 01:33:20,830
这就是你求我回去工作的办法？
Is that your move to get me back at my desk?

2099
01:33:22,340 --> 01:33:23,750
你想让我面对摄像头
You want me in front of a camera

2100
01:33:23,840 --> 01:33:25,130
和弗兰克·麦吉尔对峙？
to counter Frank McGill?

2101
01:33:30,850 --> 01:33:34,340
我甚至想过 这一切都是你策划的
It even crossed my mind that this was all you.

2102
01:33:35,980 --> 01:33:37,220
你只是没想到
You just didn't account

2103
01:33:37,350 --> 01:33:38,850
在我身后真的出现了一个持枪的人
for an armed civilian right behind me.

2104
01:33:40,190 --> 01:33:41,180
埃斯米…
Esme...

2105
01:33:41,230 --> 01:33:42,730
我会继续战斗的 伊丽莎白
I'll keep fighting, Elizabeth.

2106
01:33:43,900 --> 01:33:45,360
只要是我能出力的地方都行
Wherever I can make a difference.

2107
01:33:47,320 --> 01:33:50,230
但前提是 离你远远的
But as far as possible away from you.

2108
01:33:54,370 --> 01:33:56,080
当你停止以尊重待人的时候
You crossed the line when you stopped

2109
01:33:56,210 --> 01:33:57,370
你就已经越界了
treating people with respect.

2110
01:33:58,880 --> 01:34:00,160
你足够聪明 一定早就意识到这一点了
You're smart enough to know that.

2111
01:34:01,880 --> 01:34:02,990
你只是不在乎罢了
You just don't care.

2112
01:34:08,890 --> 01:34:10,880
谢谢 谢谢大家 欢迎回来
Thank you, thank you. Welcome back.

2113
01:34:11,100 --> 01:34:12,380
我们的下一位嘉宾
Our next guest this morning is

2114
01:34:12,510 --> 01:34:13,670
是那种在你下班回家路上
the kind of guy you'd want to have around

2115
01:34:13,720 --> 01:34:15,550
突然遇见一个人 拿枪指着你的脸
when you're walking home from work one night

2116
01:34:15,770 --> 01:34:17,680
你一定希望他出现在你身边的人
and some dude sticks a gun in your face.

2117
01:34:17,770 --> 01:34:19,010
在结束了军旅生涯之后
After his military career,

2118
01:34:19,020 --> 01:34:20,600
麦吉尔做了一名商业飞行员…
McGill worked as a commercial pilot...

2119
01:34:20,730 --> 01:34:22,560
各位 面对现实吧 现在大街上已经不安全了
Let's face it, folks, the streets ain't safe.

2120
01:34:22,610 --> 01:34:24,310
要不是我们接下来这位勇敢 无畏
And if it wasn't for the courage, bravery,

2121
01:34:24,400 --> 01:34:26,480
且枪法准的嘉宾
and damn fine aim of our next guest,

2122
01:34:27,700 --> 01:34:30,450
就会有另一场悲剧发生
we'd be reflecting on yet another tragedy.

2123
01:34:30,450 --> 01:34:32,230
女士们先生们 掌声欢迎
Ladies and gentlemen, please welcome

2124
01:34:32,370 --> 01:34:34,950
最近的大红人 弗兰克·麦吉尔
the man of the moment, Frank McGill.

2125
01:34:38,210 --> 01:34:41,660
弗兰克·麦吉尔 你真是全美英雄
So, Frank McGill, all-American hero.

2126
01:34:41,920 --> 01:34:43,500
算不上 我只是一个在
Not at all. An ordinary guy

2127
01:34:43,590 --> 01:34:45,090
合适的时间 合适的地点 出现了的普通人
in the right place at the right time.

2128
01:34:45,250 --> 01:34:47,120
在他的皮带下面 放了一颗子弹
TALK SHOW HOST 1 With a 9 milli. under his belt.

2129
01:34:47,420 --> 01:34:51,340
我很好奇 你之前救的那个人曾领导过
I'm curious. The person whose life you saved once campaigned

2130
01:34:51,430 --> 01:34:53,670
废除携带枪支条令的活动
for a ban on concealed carry.

2131
01:34:53,760 --> 01:34:55,250
你对此作何感想？
How do you feel about that?

2132
01:34:55,390 --> 01:34:57,430
我很反对这样的观点
I respectfully disagree with those views.

2133
01:34:57,560 --> 01:34:59,300
但那位小姐有权利坚持自己的主观
But the young lady is entitled to her opinion

2134
01:34:59,640 --> 01:35:01,350
没有人可以因为这一点 而去攻击她
and nobody should be attacking her for that,

2135
01:35:01,810 --> 01:35:03,140
更别说拿枪去威胁她
much less holding her at gunpoint.

2136
01:35:04,110 --> 01:35:05,770
麦吉尔是上帝的礼物
McGill's a gift from God.

2137
01:35:07,440 --> 01:35:08,940
但效应并不会长久
But it won't last forever.

2138
01:35:09,950 --> 01:35:11,480
我们在计划来发大的
We're looking to parlay that

2139
01:35:11,660 --> 01:35:13,270
更进一步地考验这个斯隆
into a closer examination of Sloane.

2140
01:35:13,530 --> 01:35:15,440
我在考虑办一场国会听证会
I'm thinking of a Congressional hearing

2141
01:35:15,580 --> 01:35:19,070
来会会她另类的游说技巧
into her unorthodox lobbying practices.

2142
01:35:20,420 --> 01:35:23,950
我肯定能找到一个愿意接受这个方案的议员
I'm sure we can find a senator who may be open to the idea.

2143
01:35:24,460 --> 01:35:26,040
你想在媒体面前泼她脏水
You want to talk trash about her in the press,

2144
01:35:26,090 --> 01:35:27,080
这是一回事
that's one thing.

2145
01:35:27,130 --> 01:35:28,870
但国会听证会需要
A Congressional hearing requires

2146
01:35:28,970 --> 01:35:31,580
我们有确实的 关于她不正当行为的证据
a convincing allegation of impropriety.

2147
01:35:31,680 --> 01:35:34,170
如果能让她脸面全无 我举双手赞成
I'd give my left nut to drag her rep through the dirt,

2148
01:35:34,300 --> 01:35:35,590
但这是不可能的事
but you're not gonna get it.

2149
01:35:35,680 --> 01:35:37,600
她是开脱罪责的专家
She's a CYA specialist.

2150
01:35:38,600 --> 01:35:40,980
我从没见过像她那样擅于卖弄学问的人…
I've never met anyone so pedantic...

2151
01:35:41,100 --> 01:35:42,470
快开始全面调查
Start an inquisition.

2152
01:35:43,980 --> 01:35:46,560
让我们看看 她究竟有多会隐藏自己的污点
Let's see how well-covered her ass really is.

2153
01:35:49,570 --> 01:35:50,650
嗨
Hi.

2154
01:35:52,200 --> 01:35:54,030
我是布鲁·沃尔什 谢谢你们能来
Pru Walsh. Thanks so much for coming over.

2155
01:35:54,280 --> 01:35:56,070
这位是来自法律部的麦克·戈登
This is Mike Gordon from our legal department.

2156
01:35:56,530 --> 01:35:57,690
这位是我们法律部的丹尼尔·波斯纳
Daniel Posner from ours.

2157
01:35:58,040 --> 01:36:00,120
斯隆女士 你是这个行业里
Miss Sloane, you're at the forefront

2158
01:36:00,200 --> 01:36:02,370
最具关注度的人物 但你的名声却很臭
of an industry with a terrible reputation.

2159
01:36:02,670 --> 01:36:03,830
你有想过为什么吗？
Do you think that's deserved?

2160
01:36:05,790 --> 01:36:07,330
这项法案在过去几年 没被推翻的唯一原因
The only reason this bill wasn't passed decades ago

2161
01:36:07,340 --> 01:36:09,120
就是它能够满足某些权势的特殊利益
is because of the power of special interests.

2162
01:36:09,260 --> 01:36:10,670
当一个说客在凑集资金时…
When a lobbyist raises finance...

2163
01:36:11,220 --> 01:36:12,500
在袭击案发生后 都没有看到
We haven't heard from Esme Manucharian

2164
01:36:12,550 --> 01:36:14,880
埃斯米·曼尼克瑞安 你有和她联系过吗？
since the attack. Are you in contact with her?

2165
01:36:16,050 --> 01:36:17,420
这是我的私事
That's a private matter.

2166
01:36:17,680 --> 01:36:19,140
我觉得非常重要的一点…
I think what's important to remember...

2167
01:36:19,140 --> 01:36:20,630
那你有跟她沟通过吗？
So have you talked to her at all?

2168
01:36:21,060 --> 01:36:23,350
值得注意的一点就是 这个弗兰克·麦吉尔
What is important to remember here is that Frank McGill

2169
01:36:23,640 --> 01:36:25,260
恰巧就是守法 并且负有责任的
is exactly the kind of law-abiding,

2170
01:36:25,690 --> 01:36:27,060
枪支拥有者
responsible gun owner

2171
01:36:27,190 --> 01:36:29,180
而这种人的权利 是受到希顿·哈里斯的保护的
whose rights the Heaton-Harris Bill protects.

2172
01:36:29,320 --> 01:36:30,930
你对发生的一切内疚吗？
Do you feel any guilt about what happened?

2173
01:36:31,320 --> 01:36:32,480
我为什么要感觉内疚？
Why would I feel guilt?

2174
01:36:32,860 --> 01:36:34,900
你让埃斯米当你们运动的门面
You made Esme the face of your campaign.

2175
01:36:35,200 --> 01:36:36,560
是你在那次辩论赛上
You thrust her into the limelight

2176
01:36:36,660 --> 01:36:37,780
把她推向风口浪尖的
that night on the debate.

2177
01:36:37,870 --> 01:36:39,530
- 我不想谈这件事  - 你也不需要回答
- I'm not talking about this.  - You don't have to.

2178
01:36:39,540 --> 01:36:40,570
对于你要让她在国家电视台露面一事
Did she know that you were going to

2179
01:36:40,580 --> 01:36:42,530
她知情吗？她有同意吗？
out her on national TV? Did she agree to that?

2180
01:36:42,830 --> 01:36:45,210
你为什么不报道一下 多数的枪支拥有者
Why not report that the majority of gun owners

2181
01:36:45,380 --> 01:36:47,080
更支持全面的背景调查呢？
favor more extensive background checks?

2182
01:36:47,210 --> 01:36:48,540
她可能整个职业生涯
She probably went her entire career

2183
01:36:48,540 --> 01:36:49,700
都在小心地守护自己这个秘密
trying to keep that a carefully guarded secret.

2184
01:36:49,750 --> 01:36:50,910
反对枪支管制的人只会用花言巧语
That the gun lobby's fear-mongering rhetoric

2185
01:36:50,960 --> 01:36:53,220
传播一些谣言 抹黑希顿·哈里斯法案
is trying to paint Heaton-Harris into something it's not.

2186
01:36:53,720 --> 01:36:55,250
你觉得是不是因为你把她的秘密揭露了
Do you think that your little revelation

2187
01:36:55,680 --> 01:36:57,260
才致使她成为被袭击目标的？
is what made her a target?

2188
01:36:57,390 --> 01:36:58,420
很明显 斯隆女士
It's clear Miss Sloane

2189
01:36:58,550 --> 01:36:59,670
现在不想谈关于曼尼克瑞安小姐的事
doesn't wish to discuss Ms. Manucharian.

2190
01:36:59,720 --> 01:37:00,800
更明显的是 你的文章
What's really clear is that

2191
01:37:00,890 --> 01:37:02,050
早就已经写好了
your article's already written.

2192
01:37:02,270 --> 01:37:03,350
别回答这个问题
Don't respond to that.

2193
01:37:03,390 --> 01:37:04,930
你的这些言论纯属肆意推测
That's purely speculative on your part.

2194
01:37:05,060 --> 01:37:06,930
- 你的领导是谁？ - 别这样
- Who's controlling you?  - Let's not do this.

2195
01:37:07,060 --> 01:37:08,800
事实就是 你根本不会知道
Look, the fact is, you have no way of knowing

2196
01:37:08,900 --> 01:37:10,100
沃尔什女士的意图…
what Ms. Walsh intends to do...

2197
01:37:10,230 --> 01:37:11,520
真正的事实是 你们对斯隆女士
The fact is that you have no interest

2198
01:37:11,570 --> 01:37:12,820
将要讲的话根本就没有兴趣
in what Miss Sloane has to say.

2199
01:37:13,190 --> 01:37:15,360
- 你怎么知道？ - 你的录音机已经关了
- And how would you know that?  - Your Dictaphone's off.

2200
01:37:20,740 --> 01:37:22,070
太丢脸了
Takedown.

2201
01:37:22,450 --> 01:37:23,780
这还算好的了
It could've been worse.

2202
01:37:23,910 --> 01:37:26,000
我现在已经发现四处事实错误了
I've got four factual errors so far.

2203
01:37:26,540 --> 01:37:27,780
这对你影响不好 莉斯
This is not good, Liz.

2204
01:37:28,080 --> 01:37:29,370
都扔进碎纸机里去吧
Dump it in the recycling.

2205
01:37:29,460 --> 01:37:30,670
还能多造几支铅笔出来
They'll make pencils out of it.

2206
01:37:31,250 --> 01:37:32,460
说不定其中一支就能
Maybe one will find its way into

2207
01:37:32,510 --> 01:37:34,250
跑到一个真正有职业道德的记者手上
the hands of a reporter with some integrity.

2208
01:37:34,590 --> 01:37:35,720
这些负面影响一会儿就过去了
It will go away.

2209
01:37:38,260 --> 01:37:39,470
好的 谢谢你
Okay, thank you.

2210
01:37:41,100 --> 01:37:42,090
再见
Bye.

2211
01:37:45,100 --> 01:37:47,470
这些议员一下子都忙起来了 也真是搞笑
Funny how all these senators are suddenly very busy.

2212
01:37:49,810 --> 01:37:51,430
真正的原因我们心知肚明
We all know why that is.

2213
01:37:55,570 --> 01:37:57,060
好吧 现在的形式很严峻
Okay, so it's not great.

2214
01:37:58,160 --> 01:38:00,070
那一千五百万能帮我们走到现在
The 15 million helped us get this far,

2215
01:38:00,160 --> 01:38:01,900
但却不足以帮助我们
but it doesn't last long when you're fighting

2216
01:38:01,990 --> 01:38:03,200
和国会最富有的团体相抗衡
the richest group on the Hill.

2217
01:38:03,490 --> 01:38:04,570
直接说正事吧
Let's get to the point.

2218
01:38:04,660 --> 01:38:06,120
到最后投票的时候 我们究竟能拿几票？
How does it shake out when it comes to the vote?

2219
01:38:06,160 --> 01:38:09,000
我们之前跟他们相差不多 但根据最近的情况推断
We'd run them close. But by latest projections,

2220
01:38:09,630 --> 01:38:11,790
到最后我们应该会少四到七票
we'll be between four to seven votes short.

2221
01:38:13,340 --> 01:38:14,870
今晚也没什么可做的了
There's nothing more we can do tonight.

2222
01:38:16,170 --> 01:38:17,380
莉斯 不必赶我们走
Liz, we don't have to leave.

2223
01:38:17,800 --> 01:38:19,130
西海岸现在还是白天
The West Coast is still awake.

2224
01:38:19,470 --> 01:38:20,580
我们可以和俄勒冈州联系
We can connect with Oregon.

2225
01:38:20,640 --> 01:38:21,970
如果我们能取得那些伐木工的支持
If we close those goddamn loggers,

2226
01:38:22,100 --> 01:38:23,470
今晚就能赢得五张选票
we could get it to five votes tonight.

2227
01:38:23,510 --> 01:38:25,510
回家休息一下吧 各位
Go home and get some rest, guys.

2228
01:38:25,640 --> 01:38:26,800
你们已经忙了一天了
You've done enough for today.

2229
01:38:27,480 --> 01:38:29,140
我等会去街上 把那些该死的印有
I'll take to the streets and rip down those

2230
01:38:29,150 --> 01:38:31,730
弗兰克·麦吉尔的海报都撕了
fucking Frank McGill posters one at a time if I have to.

2231
01:38:32,150 --> 01:38:33,980
回家吧 养精蓄锐
Go home, sharpen your knives.

2232
01:38:34,440 --> 01:38:35,730
明天还要苦战呢
It'll still be on tomorrow.

2233
01:39:09,230 --> 01:39:10,640
我们继续努力
So we keep on fighting.

2234
01:39:11,350 --> 01:39:12,840
不然还能怎么办
That's all we can do.

2235
01:39:13,690 --> 01:39:15,150
我的前妻也经常这么说
As my ex-wife used to say.

2236
01:39:20,070 --> 01:39:21,480
你以前是干资金凑集的
I met you running from a fundraiser.

2237
01:39:23,200 --> 01:39:24,440
并不需要干这种事
You could be done with all this.

2238
01:39:25,910 --> 01:39:27,200
你为什么不选择退出？
Why don't you quit?

2239
01:39:31,750 --> 01:39:33,160
退出之后干嘛？
And do what?

2240
01:39:48,180 --> 01:39:49,510
晚安
Good night.

2241
01:40:25,090 --> 01:40:26,250
喂？
Hello?

2242
01:40:27,930 --> 01:40:29,340
真惊讶 你居然接了
I'm surprised you picked up.

2243
01:40:31,930 --> 01:40:33,470
抱歉 你打错了
I'm sorry, you have the wrong number.

2244
01:41:50,180 --> 01:41:52,760
她经常占国会议员的便宜
She'd ply Congressmen with benefits,

2245
01:41:53,390 --> 01:41:56,630
免费的午餐 晚会门票 以及高尔夫周末
free meals, tickets to events, golfing weekends.

2246
01:41:56,770 --> 01:41:59,180
全都是由我们的客户付的钱
All paid for by our clients, via the firm.

2247
01:41:59,270 --> 01:42:00,730
这条线索足够了吧
Well, that right there's enough.

2248
01:42:00,820 --> 01:42:02,560
她一定会要求我们出示收据的
She'd make a point of invoicing them,

2249
01:42:02,730 --> 01:42:04,470
但没人以为自己会付钱
though they were never expected to pay.

2250
01:42:05,030 --> 01:42:06,900
债务部分在我们的资产负债表上并没有明确表示
The debt shows as an asset on our balance sheet.

2251
01:42:06,900 --> 01:42:08,770
这样我们才能适时对它进行修改
We can call it in any time we want.

2252
01:42:08,870 --> 01:42:10,900
你当她助手当了两年
You were her right hand for two years.

2253
01:42:12,870 --> 01:42:15,030
一定有什么我们遗漏了的
There's got to be something.

2254
01:42:17,500 --> 01:42:18,950
她的档案上为什么没出现任何名字？
Why's nobody on her files?

2255
01:42:19,040 --> 01:42:21,370
有很多我们的人 但其余的都被删除了
There were a ton of us, but the others got pulled out.

2256
01:42:21,380 --> 01:42:23,120
看样子我们很难有所发现了
It's not like we're in danger of finding anything.

2257
01:42:23,170 --> 01:42:24,330
你现在有什么进展？
Well, how far d'you get?

2258
01:42:24,420 --> 01:42:25,960
我查找了她跳槽之前
We worked backwards from her last deal

2259
01:42:26,090 --> 01:42:27,210
接的最后一笔单子
before she jumped ship.

2260
01:42:27,300 --> 01:42:28,510
他们说最好能从最近的事上
They said it'd be better if we can

2261
01:42:28,550 --> 01:42:29,710
找出些端倪
nail her on something recent.

2262
01:42:29,760 --> 01:42:31,920
- 比如？ - “西玛洛蛋糕”
- Which was?  - Shmallow Cakes.

2263
01:42:32,060 --> 01:42:33,090
跟税金有关
Some tax thing.

2264
01:42:33,180 --> 01:42:35,090
她进行到一半就终止了
She left halfway through.

2265
01:42:35,180 --> 01:42:36,760
我怎么记得是叫什么棕榈油
I thought it was the palm oil thing.

2266
01:42:36,930 --> 01:42:37,920
棕榈油？
Palm oil?

2267
01:42:38,020 --> 01:42:39,260
能多益税金
Nutella Tax.

2268
01:42:40,690 --> 01:42:41,800
等一下
Hold on.

2269
01:42:43,110 --> 01:42:44,810
印尼？
The Indonesians?

2270
01:42:44,900 --> 01:42:46,390
我怎么不记得了
I don't remember seeing that.

2271
01:42:54,200 --> 01:42:55,360
你在找什么？
What are you looking for?

2272
01:42:59,210 --> 01:43:00,410
杜邦先生
Mr. Dupont,

2273
01:43:01,130 --> 01:43:02,740
她违反了参议院道德准则
she's in breach of Senate Ethics rules.

2274
01:43:03,460 --> 01:43:04,540
我们有证据
We can prove it.

2275
01:43:24,480 --> 01:43:27,100
这段时间你的状态不是很好啊 罗恩
Things not looking so good for you this cycle, Ron.

2276
01:43:29,490 --> 01:43:32,400
你要问我的话 我觉得你需要多看看付费电视
You ask me, you're gonna need a lot more paid media.

2277
01:43:32,950 --> 01:43:34,030
我没问你
I didn't ask you.

2278
01:43:34,080 --> 01:43:38,940
快想想谁能帮你搞定那些电视节目？
Now, who might just be able to fund those coveted TV spots?

2279
01:43:39,330 --> 01:43:41,040
我是支持希顿·哈里斯的
I'm committed to Heaton-Harris,

2280
01:43:41,290 --> 01:43:43,000
我不能说一套
I can't vote for it with one hand

2281
01:43:43,380 --> 01:43:44,870
背后做一套
and choke it with the other.

2282
01:43:44,960 --> 01:43:46,950
你当然可以 只需要打着公正的幌子
Under cover of impartiality, sure you can.

2283
01:43:47,510 --> 01:43:50,500
你曾经可是名噪一时的说客
You've been a vocal critic of lobbyists in the past.

2284
01:43:50,720 --> 01:43:53,550
你要发起一项针对斯隆的调查
You'll lead an inquiry into Sloane's affairs

2285
01:43:53,640 --> 01:43:55,880
借以回应近来越来越被媒体关注的
in response to growing media pressure

2286
01:43:56,140 --> 01:43:58,300
她所犯下的罪行
regarding her litany of misdeeds.

2287
01:43:58,930 --> 01:44:03,300
举办听证会的钱 可都来自老百姓的钱包
The cost of hearings is paid from the public purse.

2288
01:44:04,060 --> 01:44:06,350
罗恩 我们的客户专门选定你
Ron, our clients have identified you

2289
01:44:06,480 --> 01:44:08,560
作为组织这场听证会的主持
as the man to pull this off.

2290
01:44:08,740 --> 01:44:09,720
如果你拒绝
If you decline,

2291
01:44:09,820 --> 01:44:11,280
我可阻止不了他们
I can't stop them from

2292
01:44:11,360 --> 01:44:13,690
对你实施经济制裁
blitzing you with negative finance.

2293
01:44:14,490 --> 01:44:17,610
除非把你榨干 不然他们是不会善罢甘休的
They won't stop until they annihilate you.

2294
01:44:19,040 --> 01:44:21,570
你知道“毁灭”的这个词的词根源于哪里吗？
You know the root of the word "annihilate"?

2295
01:44:22,670 --> 01:44:23,780
拉丁文
It's Latin.

2296
01:44:25,330 --> 01:44:27,460
是“不惜一切代价消灭”的意思
It means, "reduce to nothing."

2297
01:44:29,260 --> 01:44:31,460
他们就会这样对你 罗恩
That's what they're going to do to you, Ron.

2298
01:44:31,550 --> 01:44:34,630
所以你要我怎么做？拿比尔·桑福德提供的好处
So, what? I'll be taking a wedge from Bill Sandford

2299
01:44:35,510 --> 01:44:36,850
然后对希顿·哈里斯
and leading the attack

2300
01:44:36,850 --> 01:44:39,050
最具关注度的倡导者 实施全面调查？
on Heaton-Harris' most visible advocate?

2301
01:44:39,140 --> 01:44:41,260
一个六年级的小学生 就会划线将点连起来
A 6th grader could connect the dots.

2302
01:44:41,350 --> 01:44:44,890
我们可以对现有的资源进行混淆
We can create a structure to obfuscate the source.

2303
01:44:45,400 --> 01:44:46,930
你将得到的好处
Your big wedge will arrive

2304
01:44:47,020 --> 01:44:50,060
将会被分成八到十二个小块 送到你手中
courtesy of eight to 12 smaller entities

2305
01:44:50,150 --> 01:44:52,110
跟枪支都毫无关系
with no affiliation to guns.

2306
01:44:55,620 --> 01:44:56,980
你说的好处究竟有多劲爆？
How big a wedge we talking?

2307
01:44:59,870 --> 01:45:01,230
劲爆到
Big enough

2308
01:45:02,080 --> 01:45:03,570
你可以选择
to be the difference between

2309
01:45:03,660 --> 01:45:05,370
继续坐在美国参议员的位置上
the continuation of your duties

2310
01:45:05,460 --> 01:45:07,120
或者选择
as a United States Senator

2311
01:45:07,840 --> 01:45:10,330
让你的职业生涯毁于一旦
and the reduction of your career to nothing.

2312
01:45:26,270 --> 01:45:27,480
这是自从两周前
This is every hit since

2313
01:45:27,560 --> 01:45:29,900
布鲁·沃尔什报道后 所发表的所有讽刺文章
the original Pru Walsh hack-job two weeks ago.

2314
01:45:30,860 --> 01:45:32,270
我个人最喜欢的是
My personal favorite is the one

2315
01:45:32,360 --> 01:45:33,400
你如何通过造谣
about how you toppled

2316
01:45:33,530 --> 01:45:34,890
你们的学生会主席作弊
the head of the High School Student Council

2317
01:45:34,900 --> 01:45:36,820
将其推翻
with a fabricated plagiarism scandal.

2318
01:45:37,620 --> 01:45:39,280
我觉得这并非诽谤
I'm assuming that's not libelous

2319
01:45:39,370 --> 01:45:40,780
因为你干得出来这种事
'cause I can totally see it.

2320
01:45:41,160 --> 01:45:42,700
那个婊子很讨人厌的
That witch was insufferable.

2321
01:45:43,750 --> 01:45:45,360
我要把你从团队中开除
I'm taking you off the campaign.

2322
01:45:45,580 --> 01:45:46,570
什么？
What?

2323
01:45:47,670 --> 01:45:49,030
不是你 是她
Not you, her.

2324
01:45:50,210 --> 01:45:51,200
我先出去了
I'll be outside.

2325
01:45:52,760 --> 01:45:54,170
你在说什么？
What are you talking about?

2326
01:45:54,260 --> 01:45:55,460
只要有你在
Heaton-Harris gets colder

2327
01:45:55,550 --> 01:45:56,960
希顿·哈里斯就日渐衰退
every day you're associated with it.

2328
01:45:57,970 --> 01:45:59,180
你和斯珀林有奸情
Sperling's got the hots for you.

2329
01:45:59,760 --> 01:46:01,470
我连见都没见过他 这是陷害
I haven't even met him, this is a setup.

2330
01:46:02,010 --> 01:46:03,300
这是他们精心策划的
If they're orchestrating it,

2331
01:46:03,390 --> 01:46:05,050
目的就是想让我被开除
it's because they want me off the campaign.

2332
01:46:07,270 --> 01:46:09,010
现在 你有一场听证会要应付
Right now, you're lawyering up for a hearing.

2333
01:46:13,740 --> 01:46:15,100
根据印度尼西亚政府
Regarding your representation

2334
01:46:15,150 --> 01:46:16,360
的陈诉
of the Indonesian government.

2335
01:46:16,450 --> 01:46:17,690
丹 你忙吗？
Dan, are you busy?

2336
01:46:17,780 --> 01:46:18,990
艾伦·雅各布议员
Senator Allen Jacobs,

2337
01:46:19,370 --> 01:46:22,610
是被你称为“能多益税金”的资助人
the sponsor of the bill you dubbed the Nutella Tax,

2338
01:46:24,910 --> 01:46:26,990
他和家人乘坐头等舱 前往印尼
was flown to Indonesia first-class with his family,

2339
01:46:27,210 --> 01:46:29,410
住的是五星级宾馆
and put up at a 5-star hotel.

2340
01:46:30,170 --> 01:46:34,080
我们的审计员预估本次旅途 共花费三万美元
Our audit puts the cost of this trip at over $30,000.

2341
01:46:34,460 --> 01:46:36,130
他回来之后
Shortly after his return,

2342
01:46:36,220 --> 01:46:38,880
很快他的提案就被搁置了
the bill was pulled from consideration.

2343
01:46:40,760 --> 01:46:42,800
这是怎么回事？
Now, why do you suppose this happened?

2344
01:46:42,890 --> 01:46:45,680
据我了解 那次旅途是带有教育目的的
I understand the trip was for educational purposes.

2345
01:46:45,770 --> 01:46:48,350
我猜测他意识到自己的提案
I can surmise that he learned how his bill

2346
01:46:48,440 --> 01:46:49,930
很可能会抑制当地基础工业的发展
would have strangled a key industry,

2347
01:46:50,020 --> 01:46:51,560
还会使数千位
and confined thousands

2348
01:46:51,650 --> 01:46:54,260
农民遭受穷苦
of impoverished farmers to destitution.

2349
01:46:54,360 --> 01:46:56,060
他是躺在自己的私人海滩上意识到的？
From his private beach?

2350
01:46:57,150 --> 01:47:00,440
真相是 你的客户资助这次旅行
No. The truth is, your client funded this trip

2351
01:47:00,620 --> 01:47:03,780
就是想让议员撤销他的提案的
as an inducement for the senator to withdraw his bill.

2352
01:47:04,160 --> 01:47:05,490
- 不是这样的吗？ - 完全不是
- Isn't that right?  - Not at all.

2353
01:47:05,580 --> 01:47:07,280
我的客户是印尼政府
My client was the Indonesian Government.

2354
01:47:07,460 --> 01:47:08,620
这次旅行是由
The trip was sponsored

2355
01:47:08,710 --> 01:47:10,370
环境研究学院赞助的
by the Institute of Environmental Studies,

2356
01:47:10,460 --> 01:47:13,540
一个非盈利的组织
a 501 C-3 non-profit organization.

2357
01:47:13,630 --> 01:47:14,740
整个旅行也是提前
Travel was pre-approved

2358
01:47:14,840 --> 01:47:16,670
通过了参议院道德委员会的允许
by the Senate Ethics Committee.

2359
01:47:16,760 --> 01:47:19,540
你的客户向这个非盈利组织捐过钱吗？
Has your client ever donated to this non-profit?

2360
01:47:20,010 --> 01:47:21,220
我不得而知
I wouldn't know that.

2361
01:47:21,300 --> 01:47:22,920
他们的捐赠人信息是不对外公开的
I'm not privy to their list of donors.

2362
01:47:23,100 --> 01:47:26,050
我也没有资格安排这样的资助
Nor had I any role in arranging funding for this.

2363
01:47:26,810 --> 01:47:28,300
- 没有资格？ - 嗯
- No role?  - Mmm.

2364
01:47:29,020 --> 01:47:31,350
那是当然 因为参议院道德准则中
Of course, you couldn't have any role

2365
01:47:31,900 --> 01:47:34,890
明文规定 作为一个说客是严禁
because the Senate Ethics rules prevent lobbyists

2366
01:47:35,230 --> 01:47:38,070
私自为国会成员安排海外旅行的
from arranging overseas travel for members of Congress.

2367
01:47:38,150 --> 01:47:39,360
没错
Indeed.

2368
01:47:43,030 --> 01:47:44,240
你知道这是什么吗？
Do you know what this is?

2369
01:47:46,410 --> 01:47:47,570
可以给你一份复印件
Perhaps we can get you a copy.

2370
01:47:55,550 --> 01:47:56,880
你对这张表格熟悉吗？
Are you familiar with that form?

2371
01:47:58,300 --> 01:48:00,160
熟悉 这是一张私人赞助的保证书
Yes. It's a Private Sponsor Certification Form.

2372
01:48:00,260 --> 01:48:01,870
这张私人赞助保证书的复印件
It's a copy of the same

2373
01:48:02,010 --> 01:48:03,720
跟雅各布议员想要去印尼前
Private Sponsor Certification Form

2374
01:48:03,800 --> 01:48:06,040
必须递交给参议院道德委员会
that was submitted to the Senate Ethics Committee

2375
01:48:06,140 --> 01:48:08,850
并得到提前授权的那张表格
to pre-authorize Senator Jacobs' travel

2376
01:48:08,980 --> 01:48:10,140
是一样的
to Indonesia.

2377
01:48:10,690 --> 01:48:13,270
看看这张表格下面的笔迹 斯隆女士
Look at the handwriting on that form, Miss Sloane.

2378
01:48:15,150 --> 01:48:16,850
你能认出这个笔迹吗？
Do you recognize that handwriting?

2379
01:48:17,730 --> 01:48:18,720
能
Yes, I do.

2380
01:48:18,820 --> 01:48:20,100
那是你的笔迹吗？
Is it your handwriting?

2381
01:48:23,110 --> 01:48:24,230
是我的
It is.

2382
01:48:26,450 --> 01:48:28,070
看来我们找到问题了
Well, it seems we have a problem.

2383
01:48:28,830 --> 01:48:30,940
虽然这张表格是由
Even though the form was signed

2384
01:48:31,040 --> 01:48:32,150
一个非盈利组织签署和归档的
and filed by the non-profit,

2385
01:48:32,290 --> 01:48:34,000
但填写的人是你
you were the one who filled it out.

2386
01:48:34,540 --> 01:48:36,160
这是能够证明你
This is prima evidence

2387
01:48:36,340 --> 01:48:38,290
私自安排国会议员海外旅行的
that you were involved in arranging

2388
01:48:38,380 --> 01:48:40,370
第一个证据
overseas travel for a member of Congress.

2389
01:48:41,170 --> 01:48:44,960
这违反了参议院道德准则
Constituting a clear breach of Senate Ethics rules.

2390
01:48:45,220 --> 01:48:46,630
这就是你们的王牌？
Is that your trump card?

2391
01:48:48,260 --> 01:48:49,470
你们把我拖来这里
You drag me in here,

2392
01:48:49,560 --> 01:48:51,670
像审讯犯人一样 窥探我的隐私
wedge an endoscope up my posterior,

2393
01:48:52,020 --> 01:48:54,560
到最后唯一能让我归罪的东西
and all this time, the only incriminating item

2394
01:48:54,650 --> 01:48:57,260
就是一堆没用的文件？
you have in your possession is a filing snafu?

2395
01:48:57,360 --> 01:48:59,220
那监控你要怎么解释 斯隆女士？
How about surveillance, Miss Sloane?

2396
01:48:59,440 --> 01:49:02,530
鲁道夫先生在法庭上作证
Mr. Rodolfo Schmidt has stated in deposition

2397
01:49:03,030 --> 01:49:05,240
说你有意图用
that you intended to use methods

2398
01:49:05,320 --> 01:49:07,030
窃听和黑客技术
such as bugging and tapping

2399
01:49:07,120 --> 01:49:10,320
借此欺诈汉克·巴杰利议员 这是真的吗？
to entrap Senator Hank Badgley. ls this true?

2400
01:49:10,500 --> 01:49:13,860
我确实有过这种想法 但那只是一瞬间的事
I did, for a brief moment, intend to use such methods.

2401
01:49:13,960 --> 01:49:15,990
这种企图并没有得到实施
But that intention was never acted upon.

2402
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:17,200
那是为什么呢？
And why was that?

2403
01:49:17,340 --> 01:49:19,250
因为被斯密特先生制止了
Mr. Schmidt expressly forbade it,

2404
01:49:19,340 --> 01:49:21,290
我相信在他的证词里应该也提到了
as he no doubt told you in his deposition.

2405
01:49:21,380 --> 01:49:22,500
但很显然你对实施这样的手段
But you were clearly comfortable

2406
01:49:22,550 --> 01:49:23,580
很是无所谓
with these methods.

2407
01:49:24,050 --> 01:49:27,290
在你的游说生涯中
Did you employ the tactics of espionage

2408
01:49:27,390 --> 01:49:29,590
是否经常雇佣间谍技术？
regularly throughout your lobbying career?

2409
01:49:29,680 --> 01:49:30,930
我没有
No, I did not.

2410
01:49:31,020 --> 01:49:32,130
那我换个问题
Then let me ask you this.

2411
01:49:32,140 --> 01:49:34,050
你是否授权 命令
Have you ever authorized, ordered,

2412
01:49:34,140 --> 01:49:35,720
或者自己对他人
or otherwise brought about

2413
01:49:35,900 --> 01:49:38,890
实施过任何一种手段的非法监控？
any kind of unlawful surveillance on any person?

2414
01:49:39,940 --> 01:49:41,930
我先提醒你 在听证会会作伪证
Let me remind you that perjury

2415
01:49:42,030 --> 01:49:43,730
可是项重罪
before Congress is a felony, which...

2416
01:49:43,820 --> 01:49:44,860
我的答案是否定的
The answer is no.

2417
01:49:46,410 --> 01:49:49,570
我从没授权过任何非法的监控行为
I have never authorized illegal surveillance.

2418
01:49:53,160 --> 01:49:55,150
这就是我想提的所有问题了
This concludes my questioning of the witness.

2419
01:49:55,250 --> 01:49:56,530
谢谢你 斯隆女士
Thank you, Miss Sloane.

2420
01:50:05,720 --> 01:50:07,170
我们还有一个证人
We have one further witness.

2421
01:50:08,930 --> 01:50:10,760
如果你说的不是假话
Either you just perjured yourself,

2422
01:50:10,850 --> 01:50:12,680
那说明你这个人 还没肮脏到那种程度
or you're not so sleazy after all.

2423
01:50:13,430 --> 01:50:15,260
传证人罗伯特·福德先生
The Committee calls Mr. Robert Forde.

2424
01:50:16,100 --> 01:50:17,430
这我可没想到
I wouldn't count on that.

2425
01:50:19,400 --> 01:50:20,600
主席先生 为什么我事先
Mr. Chairman, I don't recall

2426
01:50:20,730 --> 01:50:22,190
没有收到通知 你要传唤…
being notified of your intention to...

2427
01:50:22,230 --> 01:50:23,270
我们是最近
We were only recently

2428
